nd desire to reconcile the appeal of modernity with the pull of traditional Judaism. The volume includes a memoir by Adena Potok and ends with Chaim Potok's "My Life as a Writer," a speech he gave at Penn State in 1982.Aside from the editor, the contributors are Victoria Aarons, Nathan P. Devir, Jane Eisner, Susanne Klingenstein, S. Lillian Kremer, Jessica Lang, Sanford E. Marovitz, Kathryn McClymond, Hugh Nissenson, Adena Potok, and Jonathan Rosen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Artists, Architects, Photographers.2bisacsh1 aAarons, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDevir, Nathan P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisner, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlingenstein, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKremer, S. Lillian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLang, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarovitz, Sanford E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcClymond, Kathryn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNissenson, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotok, Adena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotok, Chaim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosen, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalden, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalden, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package Pr